SESSION.DESCRIPTION:
Perform validation against claims in RCNT_RECN_DSTR_TXN_STG tables for outcome or post apc distributions. If any claim has error, then update the distribution status to ERROR, update RECN_ERR_CD on table RCNT_RECN_DSTR_TXN_STG to 1. An error file will be created inlcuding recn gid, dstr gid, period id. Also an error parm file will be created.
Possible errors: admin amt is out of balance (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) base amt is out of balance (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) contract amt is out of balance (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) frmly amt is out of balance (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) perf amt is out of balance (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) prc ptct amt is out of balance (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) NDC is null (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) external src is null (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) PICO is null (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) AP COMPANY CD is null (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) Rebate ID is null (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) period is null (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM or VRAP.RCNT_RECN_HDR) CM Approval timestamp is null (VRAP.RCNT_RECN_APRV_DSTR_DTL where APRV_ROLE_CD = 6 POST_DT is null (VRAP.RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR) No claim included in distribution (VRAP.RCNT_RECN_DSTR_TXN_STG)
When it fails, it sends out a failure email and update RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR status to ERROR.
Added as part of ITPR017177 - CV Rewrite Project: Removed the error validations for all 6 revenue buckets, because now , over payment and under adjustments are allowed.

The mapping %m ran in the %s session in the %w workflow ran in %d.
ONCALL: This process runs every 30 minutes to process any Distribution in VRAP.RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR table with DSTR_STAT_CD = 10 - READY TO TRANSMIT.
The process changes DSTR_STAT_CD to 15 - TRANSMITTING right after it starts and changes it to 99 - ERROR if failed or if any Distribution inludes one or more error claims.
Please research on the cause of the failure. To rerun the workflow, 1. reset DSTR_STAT_CD in table RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR with status of 99 - ERROR and/or 15 - TRANSMITTING (in case it failed to update to ERROR) updated from this run with the latest UPDT_TS, to status of 10 - READY TO TRANSMIT. 2. reset the failed Process Controler entry status to NEW to rerun the process from the top.
Target Table: %t
%l
%r
Session Log is attached %g

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This session runs if session s_m_CASH_Txn_Validation or s_m_CASH_Txn_Validation fails during execution. It updates the RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR status to ERROR.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_CASH_Txn_Update_GDX_Dstr_Hdr_Cntl_Failure

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION:
Perform validation against claims in RCNT_RECN_DSTR_TXN_STG tables for outcome or post apc distributions. If any claim has error, then update the distribution status to ERROR, update RECN_ERR_CD on table RCNT_RECN_DSTR_TXN_STG to 1. An error file will be created inlcuding recn gid, dstr gid, period id. Also an error parm file will be created.
Possible errors: admin amt is out of balance (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) base amt is out of balance (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) contract amt is out of balance (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) frmly amt is out of balance (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) perf amt is out of balance (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) prc ptct amt is out of balance (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) NDC is null (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) external src is null (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) PICO is null (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) AP COMPANY CD is null (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) Rebate ID is null (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM) period is null (VRAP.RCNT_EXTN_CLM or VRAP.RCNT_RECN_HDR) CM Approval timestamp is null (VRAP.RCNT_RECN_APRV_DSTR_DTL where APRV_ROLE_CD = 6 POST_DT is null (VRAP.RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR) No claim included in distribution (VRAP.RCNT_RECN_DSTR_TXN_STG)
When it fails, it sends out a failure email and update RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR status to ERROR.
Added as part of ITPR017177 - CV Rewrite Project: Removed the error validations for all 6 revenue buckets, because now , over payment and under adjustments are allowed.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_CASH_Txn_Validation

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION:
Populate RCNT_RECN_PMT_DSTR_DTL table with claims belong to outcome or post apc distribution. The record will be broken into per claim and trans type. It takes the error parm file and set the error parm $$ERR_CLM_EXIST on the same workflow variable to be used to execute session s_m_CASH_Error to send the error data file.
When it fails, it sends out a failure email and update RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR status to ERROR.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_CASH_Txn_Insert_GDX_PMT_DSTR_DTL

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This session only runs when $$ERR_CLM_EXIST=1. It'll send the error detail data file cash_dstr_txn_err_data.dat as attachments to _GDXITD to research.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: s_m_CASH_Error_Email
